---
layout: base.njk
permalink: style-prototypes.html
bodyClass: example-body
pageHeader: Style Prototypes
title: Visual Style Prototypes
description: Technical Figure dialect with accent palette comparison for Preposition Programming sketches.
loadP5: true
---
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ '/styles/style-prototypes.css' | url }}">

<article class="prototype-matrix-page">
  <section class="prototype-intro">
    <div class="decision-banner">
      <strong>Selected dialect:</strong> Technical Figure — grid-backed coordinate space, dashed dimensions, figure tags.
    </div>
    <h2>Choose an accent palette</h2>
    <p>The structure is set. Compare four accent treatments below (same Technical Figure layout on Above, Toward, and Before). Pick one to lock in the styleguide.</p>
    <a class="prototype-guide-link" href="{{ '/docs/visual-styleguide.md' | url }}">View styleguide (markdown)</a>
  </section>

  <div class="color-palette-matrix" aria-label="Accent palette comparison">
    <div class="matrix-corner"></div>

    {% set palettes = [
      { id: "monochrome", name: "Ink Only", hex: "#111111", note: "No spot color — weight & fill only" },
      { id: "blueprint", name: "Blueprint Blue", hex: "#2B5F8C", note: "Technical manual / coordinate blue" },
      { id: "sepia", name: "Sepia Ink", hex: "#7D5A2A", note: "Warm lithograph brown" },
      { id: "vermillion", name: "Vermillion", hex: "#C0392B", note: "High-contrast annotation red" }
    ] %}
    {% for pal in palettes %}
    <div class="matrix-col-header matrix-col-header--color">
      <span class="color-swatch" style="background: {{ pal.hex }}"></span>
      <h3>{{ pal.name }}</h3>
      <p class="color-hex">{{ pal.hex }}</p>
      <p>{{ pal.note }}</p>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}

    {% set examples = [
      { id: "above", title: "Above", cat: "Spatial", note: "Y-axis height comparison" },
      { id: "toward", title: "Toward", cat: "Movement", note: "Vector toward target" },
      { id: "before", title: "Before", cat: "Time", note: "Clear path, then move" }
    ] %}

    {% for ex in examples %}
    <div class="matrix-row-header">
      <div class="row-category">{{ ex.cat }}</div>
      <h3>{{ ex.title }}</h3>
      <p>{{ ex.note }}</p>
    </div>
    {% for pal in palettes %}
    <div class="prototype-cell" data-style-label="{{ pal.name }}">
      <div id="color-{{ pal.id }}-{{ ex.id }}" class="prototype-cell__canvas" aria-label="{{ ex.title }} — {{ pal.name }}"></div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <section class="style-notes">
    <h2>Palette notes</h2>

    <div class="style-note-card">
      <h3><span class="color-swatch color-swatch--inline" style="background:#111111"></span> Ink Only</h3>
      <p class="style-note-sub">Pure greyscale on grid</p>
      <p>Active elements use heavier strokes and filled ink silhouettes — no chromatic accent at all. Most faithful to printed plates; relies on weight and position for emphasis.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="style-note-card style-note-card--recommended">
      <h3><span class="color-swatch color-swatch--inline" style="background:#2B5F8C"></span> Blueprint Blue <span class="tag-recommended">recommended</span></h3>
      <p class="style-note-sub">Prussian blue accent on grid</p>
      <p>Reads as “geometry” and “measurement” — natural for coordinate labels, vectors, and Δy. Less aggressive than red on instructional copy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="style-note-card">
      <h3><span class="color-swatch color-swatch--inline" style="background:#7D5A2A"></span> Sepia Ink</h3>
      <p class="style-note-sub">Warm single-ink accent</p>
      <p>Brown spot color evokes aged textbook lithography. Distinct from grey forms without the urgency of red.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="style-note-card">
      <h3><span class="color-swatch color-swatch--inline" style="background:#C0392B"></span> Vermillion</h3>
      <p class="style-note-sub">Annotation red (initial prototype)</p>
      <p>Maximum contrast for active relationships. Can feel like warnings or corrections rather than neutral diagram notation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <details class="archive-matrix">
    <summary>Earlier dialect comparison (Engraving / Technical / Minimal)</summary>
    <div class="style-prototype-matrix style-prototype-matrix--archived" aria-label="Archived style comparison">
      <div class="matrix-corner"></div>
      {% set styles = [
        { id: "engraving", name: "Engraving", sub: "Classical Plate" },
        { id: "technical", name: "Technical Figure", sub: "Annotated Diagram" },
        { id: "minimal", name: "Modern Minimal", sub: "Clean Schematic" }
      ] %}
      {% for s in styles %}
      <div class="matrix-col-header"><h3>{{ s.name }}</h3><p>{{ s.sub }}</p></div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% for ex in examples %}
      <div class="matrix-row-header">
        <div class="row-category">{{ ex.cat }}</div>
        <h3>{{ ex.title }}</h3>
        <p>{{ ex.note }}</p>
      </div>
      {% for s in styles %}
      <div class="prototype-cell">
        <div id="proto-{{ s.id }}-{{ ex.id }}" class="prototype-cell__canvas"></div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </details>
</article>

<script type="module" src="{{ '/js/style-prototypes/mount.js' | url }}"></script>
